e reset handles the initial condition correctly. We will initialize state to S0 in the reset block.\n6. **Sticky Output:** The output logic ensures that once in S4, `start_shifting` stays 1, even if the input sequence is broken later, fulfilling the 'forever until reset' requirement.\n\n*Self-Correction on Output Logic:* The requirement states: 'When the sequence is found, it should set start_shifting to 1, forever, until reset.' This implies a latching behavior based on the state entering S4. A registered output driven by the current state (`state == S_FOUND`) is the standard way to implement this sticky behavior synchronously.",
